	abstract = {Aims. A theoretical framework is developed to estimate the optimal binning of X-ray spectra. Methods. We derived expressions for the optimal bin size for model spectra as well as for observed data using diﬀerent levels of sophistication. Results. It is shown that by taking into account both the number of photons in a given spectral model bin and their average energy over the bin size, the number of model energy bins and the size of the response matrix can be reduced by a factor of 10−100. The response matrix should then contain the response at the bin centre as well as its derivative with respect to the incoming photon energy. We provide practical guidelines for how to construct optimal energy grids as well as how to structure the response matrix. A few examples are presented to illustrate the present methods.},
