radio and X-ray surface brightness correlation on frequency are interpreted in the context of turbulent reacceleration models. Under this scenario, our results allowed us to constrain that the turbulent kinetic pressure of the ICM is up to 10\%.},
	urldate = {2021-10-22},
	journal = {Astronomy \& Astrophysics},
	author = {Rajpurohit, K. and Brunetti, G. and Bonafede, A. and van Weeren, R. J. and Botteon, A. and Vazza, F. and Hoeft, M. and Riseley, C. J. and Bonnassieux, E. and Brienza, M. and Forman, W. R. and Röttgering, H. J. A. and Rajpurohit, A. S. and Locatelli, N. and Shimwell, T. W. and Cassano, R. and Di Gennaro, G. and Brüggen, M. and Wittor, D. and Drabent, A. and Ignesti, A.},
	month = feb,
